gh offering credit for feeding back to grid during peak hours and emergency islanding conditions. This is possible through smart integration of EV with conventional grid through two-way (electrical and information) communication between a distribution utility and consumer. This paper highlights the challenges posed by the emergent requirement of EVs and smart grid solutions to overcome the hurdles of peak demand, renewable uncertainty, etc. © Springer Nature Singapore Pte Ltd. 2018.},
